title: SpaceX’s NASA Psyche Falcon Heavy launch slips to September
summary: SpaceX’s first dedicated Falcon Heavy launch for NASA has been hit by a seven-week delay after spacecraft engineers discovered a software anomaly...

title: Starliner concludes OFT-2 test flight with landing in New Mexico
summary: Boeing’s CST-100 Starliner safely landed in New Mexico May 25, concluding a six-day uncrewed test flight to the International Space Station.

title: Gogo’s OneWeb partnership could face Starlink in business aviation market
summary: Gogo is planning to use OneWeb satellites in a partnership that could see it take on Starlink in an emerging business aviation market for low Earth orbit services.

title: NASA Administrator, Arizona Students to Hear from Station Astronauts
summary: Students from Arizona will have an opportunity this week to hear from astronauts aboard the International Space Station.

title: Virgin Orbit expects first U.K. launch in August
summary: Virgin Orbit expects to perform its first launch from England in late August, pending award of a British launch license, a company executive said May 25.
